ImportGenius Data Removal Guide
================================

Overview
--------
ImportGenius provides trade data and market intelligence based on US import/export records. This guide covers their data removal procedures.

About ImportGenius
-------------------
- Aggregates US customs and shipping data
- Provides detailed company trade profiles
- Offers market analysis and competitor intelligence
- Widely used for business development and market research

Data Removal Process
--------------------

Step 1: Data Assessment
- Search your company across ImportGenius platform
- Identify specific records, profiles, and reports
- Document URLs and data points for removal
- Check for subsidiary and related entity data

Step 2: Contact ImportGenius
- Primary contact: support@importgenius.com
- Subject: "Data Removal Request - [Company Name]"
- Include specific record URLs and business justification
- Provide verification of authority to request removal

Step 3: Provide Documentation
- Business license or incorporation documents
- Letter of authorization (if requesting on behalf of client)
- Specific privacy or business concerns
- References to applicable data protection regulations

Step 4: Follow Removal Process
- Submit formal written request
- Respond to verification inquiries promptly
- Track removal progress and timelines
- Confirm completion of removal

Key Considerations
------------------
- ImportGenius distinguishes between public record data and their value-added analysis
- Some public record information may not be removable
- Removal typically takes 2-3 weeks after verification
- New trade activity may result in new data appearing

Best Practices
--------------
- Be specific about which data elements to remove
- Explain business impact and privacy concerns
- Maintain professional communication throughout
- Document all correspondence for future reference
- Set up monitoring for new data exposure

Common Removal Challenges
-------------------------
- Verification of requestor authority
- Distinguishing removable vs. non-removable public data
- Handling of related entity and subsidiary data
- Managing timing with ongoing business operations

Sample Request Template
-----------------------
"Subject: Data Removal Request - [Company Name]

Dear ImportGenius Team,

We request removal of [Company Name] data from your platform due to competitive sensitivity and business privacy concerns. Specific areas of concern include:

- Company trade profiles
- Supplier/customer relationship data  
- Historical shipping patterns
- Contact information and business details

We have attached verification documents and are available to provide additional information as needed. Please confirm receipt and provide expected timeline for completion.

Thank you for your attention to this matter."

Important Notes
---------------
- Keep copies of all removal requests and responses
- Monitor for data reappearance after removal
- Consider proactive measures (manifest confidentiality) for ongoing protection
- Professional removal services may be beneficial for complex cases

